#: ../../language/error_codes/E4073.md:1
msgid "E4073"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4073.md:3
msgid "Cannot provide default implementation for traits from other packages."
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4073.md:5
msgid ""
"This is a corollary of the [orphan rules of traits and types in "
"MoonBit](../packages.md#trait-implementations). Default implementation "
"can be seen as implementing the trait for all possible types, including "
"types defined within or outside of current package. Therefore, it is only"
" possible for default implementation to be defined in the package of the "
"trait, otherwise it would violate the orphan rules."
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4073.md:12
msgid "Erroneous example"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4073.md:14
msgid ""
"Suppose you have a trait `T` defined in package `a` in module "
"`username/hello`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4073.md:16
msgid "`a/a.mbt`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4073.md:18
msgid ""
"// We need the trait to be pub(open) so that it can be implemented from "
"outside.\n"
"pub(open) trait T {\n"
"  f(Self) -> Int\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4073.md:22
msgid ""
"And when you want to define a default implementation for the trait in "
"another package, say `b`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4073.md:25
msgid "`b/moon.pkg.json`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4073.md:27
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"import\": [\n"
"    \"username/hello/a\"\n"
"  ]\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4073.md:35
#: ../../language/error_codes/E4073.md:47
msgid "`b/b.mbt`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4073.md:37
msgid ""
"impl @a.T with f(self : Self) -> Int {\n"
"  //           ^\n"
"  // Error: Cannot provide default implementation for trait @a.T from "
"package a\n"
"  ignore(self)\n"
"  0\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4073.md:41
msgid "Suggestion"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4073.md:43
msgid ""
"To fix this error, you can move the definition of the trait and the "
"default implementation of this trait into the same package. Say you can "
"move the trait definition into package `b`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E4073.md:49
msgid ""
"pub(open) trait T {\n"
"  f(Self) -> Int\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"impl T with f(self : Self) -> Int {\n"
"  ignore(self)\n"
"  0\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

